article.headline: Rhode Island defeats McNeese State 76-71
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- Xavier Munford scored 26 points and made a game-high six 3-pointers Tuesday night to lead Rhode Island to a 76-71 victory over McNeese State. Munford had 13 points in the first half and has scored in double figures in seven of eight games. Rhode Island (6-2) led by 21 points after a 3-point shot by Jarelle Reischel with 12:45 remaining. McNeese State erased the lead to close within three points at 72-69 with 20 seconds remaining. Reischel and Gilvydas Biruta each made two free throws in the closing seconds to give the Rams their third-straight win. Biruta scored 17 points and Reischel added 11. Rhode Island had a season-high 16 assists, Biggie Minnis led with eight. Kevin Hardy was 11 of 27 from the floor and scored a career-high 24 points to lead McNeese State (2-5).
